This year , many travel companies are featuring trips that focus on adventures of the mind and exploration of cultures throughout the world .
For example , TraveLearn , a Lakeville , Pa . - based company , seasons its travel programs with on-site lectures ; field experiences conducted by local experts ; and opportunities to meet and mingle with the locals _ say , a meal with a Moroccan family .
Tour groups vary in size from eight to 20 people with college faculty escorts .
Some of the 18 tours offered this year include stops in Antarctica , China , the Galapagos , Ireland and Nova Scotia .
Prices are from $ 2,000 to $ 5,000 and include airfare from departure cities .
For more information , write TraveLearn , P.O .
Box 315 , Lakeville , Pa. 18438 ; call ( 800 ) 235 - 9114 ; or visit their Web site at www.travelearn.com .
-- -- -
Senior Summer School provides a choice of college-level travel programs that cater to the mature set at five U.S. universities in the cities of Los Angeles , San Diego and Santa Barbara , Calif. ; New Brunswick , Canada ; and Madison , Wis.
The programs vary in duration from two weeks ( $ 500 ) to eight weeks ( $ 2,900 ) and include accommodations , meals , courses and related trips , social events and some weekend activities .
Accommodations will be at university dormitories or residence halls .
For more information , write to Senior Summer School , P.O .
Box 4424 , Deerfield Beach , Fla. 33442 ; call ( 800 ) 847 - 2466 ; or visit their Web site at www.seniorsummerschool.com .
-- -- -
The Maui Writers Conference is the place to be for mature travelers who have a writerly flair .
Slated for Sept. 4 to 7 and preceded by a retreat Aug. 29 to Sept. 3 , the conference promises aspiring writers the opportunity to mingle with publishing experts , `` rent '' an agent for 15 minutes , have a manuscript evaluated and listen to some great speakers , from Pulitzer Prize-winner Dave Barry to Robert Loomis , vice president of Random House .
Accommodations will be at the Grand Wailea Resort or Aston Wailea .
The conference registration is $ 500 if postmarked by July 1 ; $ 600 thereafter .
Consultations and evaluations are extra , as are airfare and hotel .
For registration forms , write P.O .
Box 1118 , Kihei , Hawaii 96753 ; call ( 808 ) 879 - 0061 ; or e-mail writers ( AT ) maui.net .
-- -- -
Familyhostel , a program sponsored by the University of New Hampshire Continuing Education , offers kids ages 8 to 15 and their grandparents the chance to learn more about the world in which they live .
Familyhostel 's summer ' 98 programs , which last 10 days , will include trips to Vienna , Austria ; Prague and the Czech Castles ; Normandy , Paris and Provence , France ; Cuernavaca and Mexico City , Mexico ; and Abergavenny and Emyln , Wales .
Familyhostel grew out of Interhostel , a travel and study abroad program for people ages 50 and older .
Familyhostel programs cost from $ 2,200 to $ 3,000 for adults and $ 2,100 to $ 2,600 for grandchildren .
Participants are assigned a pre-trip reading list and are asked to create a scrapbook during the trip .
For more information , write Familyhostel , UNH Continuing Education , 6 Garrison Ave. , Durham , N.H .
03824 ; call ( 800 ) 733 - 9753 ; or visit their Web site at www.learn.unh.edu .
-- -- -
For September , Elderhostel is offering a new two-week cultural exploration of Ghana , West Africa , called African Music and Dance .
This educational program , which is designed specifically for those ages 55 and older , costs $ 3,000 from New York or $ 3,300 from Los Angeles and includes airfare .
This program is an intensive introduction to Ghana , its history and people and uses music and dance as the vehicle for discovery .
Participants will dance , sing and learn about the Ghanaian way of life , according to Kwame Agyapong , the program coordinator .
For more information , write to Elderhostel , Dept. J3 , P.O .
Box 1959 , Wakefield , Mass. 01880 - 5959 ; or call ( 617 ) 426 - 7788
-- -- -
Educational travel experiences that enable travelers to meet famous authors are what make Saga Holidays ' Roads Scholar program so special .
Among the new 1998 offerings is a 16-night program called British Landscapes and Literature , with accommodations at the campus of the Oatridge Agriculture College in Oatridge , Scotland , and in the Lake District of England .
In Scotland , there will be lectures about Robert the Bruce and William Wallace .
In England , the topic will be the Lake poets , William Wordsworth and Samuel Taylor Coleridge .
Rates , based on single occupancy , start at $ 2,400 per person , including airfare .
For details , call ( 800 ) 621 - 2151 .
-- -- -
`` Berlin , A Commemorative Tour on the 50th Anniversary of the Airlift , '' is one of the historic adventures offered this year by Specialty Tours Ltd.
Specialty Tours , in association with the City of Berlin and military historical groups , offers a trip that will allow seniors the chance to share with their grandchildren a part of history that shaped the world .
The 13-day trip departs June 22 and costs $ 2,400 per person .
It will include sightseeing in Berlin , Fassburg , Frankfurt and Wiesbaden .
For more information , contact Specialty Tours Ltd. at 6535 Copa Ct . , Falls Church , Va. 22044 ; or call ( 888 ) 868 - 7706 .
-- -- -
Colorado is the classroom for mature travelers ages 50 and older at `` Explore ' 98 , '' to be held in Beaver Creek , Colo. , Oct. 4 to 10 .
Actual classrooms are a cozy library , a mountain cabin , a gold-medal trout stream or an historic working ranch .
Explore 's faculty leads small classes in academic , creative and physical activities that include photography , gourmet cooking , fly fishing and astronomy .
Special events planned this year are `` The October Sky , '' a telescope viewing with astrophysicist Dennis Ebbets .
Program originator Vonnie Wheeler says participants can create schedules to suit their own pace and can choose a single subject or sample many .
Explore uses the Hyatt Regency Beaver Creek Resort as its home base .
The cost is $ 1,900 per person for those staying at the Hyatt or $ 1,500 for those with their own accommodations .
For more information , call ( 800 ) 298 - 4242 .
-- -- -
The Greek island town of Poros is the site of the Alumni Campus Abroad program offered by AHI International Corp.
Poros was the retreat of novelist Henry Miller and Greek poet George Seferis .
A unique feature of this trip includes a `` Meet the People '' panel discussion , which gives tour-goers a chance to learn more about the area from the locals .
Tours include a trip to the historical cities of Epidauros , Mycenae and Nauplion along with journeys to the ruins of Trizina , the Monastery of Poros and Sanctuary of Poseidon .
Priced at $ 2 , 300 , the tour leaves from most gateways weekly through early November .
For more information .
call ( 800 ) 323 - 7373 or write AHI International Corp. , 701 Lee St. , Des Plaines , Ill. 60016 .
